INSTRUCTIONS

Put this directory in your home directory. You should have '/home/YOU/chrome_nm/*' which contains all the files in this directory.

Make sure you have the following programs installed:
python (installed by default in most Linux distro's)

google-chrome:
   wget -q -O - https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo apt-key add -
   sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main" >> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list'
   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get install google-chrome-stable
   
For Smart card support - Ubuntu:
	pip
		sudo apt-get install python-pip
	   
	pykcs11
		sudo pip install pykcs11
	   
	python OpenSSL
		sudo pip install pyopenssl
   
For attestation Ubuntu:
	tpm-tools
	   sudo apt-get install tpm-tools

	trousers
	   sudo apt-get install trousers

	python-tk
		sudo apt-get install python-tk

  
	tpm-quote-tools
	   download this --> https://sourceforge.net/projects/tpmquotetools/
	   tar xvf tpm*
	   ./configure
	   make
	   sudo make install


	Then:
	Run the installation script.
	sudo ./chrome_nm_install.sh

	Don't forget to make an AIK! You can do so by running the following commands.
	cd /home/$username/chrome_nm/tpm && tpm_mkaik tpm_key.blob tpm_key.pubk
	cp tpm_key.pubk $(sha256sum uuid.txt | cut -d" " -f 1).pubk

	After creation, you will need to load the AIK into the TPM by running "tpm_loadkey" on the created "tpm_key.blob" file.

	Any files that are being measured must be set to global readable. (i.e. "cd /boot && sudo chmod +r *")

Other - Windows:
	Add *.bat to the executable name in the *win.json file
	